# build/container/.env.example
#
# Copy to build/container/.env (or export these as shell vars, or let
# scripts/deploy-container.sh compute them for you) before running
# `docker compose -f build/container/compose.yml up`.
#
# docs/plans/volume-only-daemon.md §論点 d / §論点 i: daemon data/config
# (BOID_DATA_DIR/BOID_CONFIG_DIR — the old host-path pair) are gone. State
# now lives in a single daemon-owned named volume (`boid_state`,
# consolidated from an earlier boid_data/boid_config split — [Major 6,
# PR829 round 1 codex review]) at the image's own fixed path
# (compose.yml's own "Persistence" header comment), so there is nothing
# for this file to say about them anymore — only the engine socket and the
# still-host-bind-mounted runtime/socket dir remain configurable here.

# Engine socket source (docs/plans/volume-only-daemon.md §論点 i, 案 X).
# Leave unset for a real docker host (defaults to /var/run/docker.sock,
# compose.yml's own in-file default) — set this only for podman rootless,
# where scripts/deploy-container.sh already computes and exports the right
# value for you (/run/user/<uid>/podman/podman.sock) when it detects
# podman; set it here only for a manual `docker compose`/`podman-compose`
# invocation that bypasses that script.
BOID_DOCKER_SOCK_SRC=/run/user/1000/podman/podman.sock

# Host path bound at the SAME path inside the container — the "server
# socket host-path mutual exclusion" mechanism (compose.yml's own comment).
# Matches client.DefaultSocketPath()'s convention: $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR, or
# /run/user/<uid> when unset. Must be the exact directory the host's own
# `boid start` (the "旧デプロイ" this stack can roll back to) would resolve
# too, or the two deploys cannot see each other's socket. Still relevant
# post-volume-only-pivot: retired once the CLI moves to a TCP profile
# default (§論点 c, a later PR), unchanged for now.
BOID_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/1000

# Must match the uid/gid build/container/Dockerfile was built with
# (BOID_UID/BOID_GID build args, default 1000:1000) AND the host uid that
# owns BOID_RUNTIME_DIR above.
BOID_UID=1000
BOID_GID=1000

# The host's `docker` group GID (Major 9, PR6 codex review). compose.yml
# adds this as a supplementary group (group_add) on the non-root daemon
# process so it can open the engine socket above — without it, every
# docker/podman API call from inside the container fails with a
# permission error. Find yours with:
#   getent group docker | cut -d: -f3
# scripts/deploy-container.sh resolves and exports this for you
# automatically; set it here only for a manual `docker compose`/
# `podman-compose` invocation.
DOCKER_GID=999
